
[1]laborious

   LABO'RIOUS, a. [L. laboriosus.]

   1. Using exertion; employing labor; diligent in work or service;
   assiduous; used of persons; as a laborious husbandman or mechanic; a
   laborious minister or pastor.

   2. Requiring labor; toilsome; tiresome; not easy; as laborious duties
   or services.

   3. Requiring labor, exertion, perseverance or sacrifices.

   Dost thou love watchings, abstinence or toil, laborious virtues all?
   Learn these from Cato.
